<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1742,2020]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[305,397,1742,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1620,1642]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,373,1599]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 20. Niphates erecta Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9895 (scale bar = 1 cm), a 1, of RMNH Por. 9877 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of cross section of peripheral skeleton of RMNH Por. 9905, c – d, SEM images of spicules, c, oxeas, d, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272971/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
d), if present, rather elongated, often provided with a faint central tyle, occasionally malformed, 14– 
